readme:
Service Usage

This service is used by the consumer to modify an earlier created referral for a specific applicant in a visa application.

Modifications include:
Adding Notes
Changing the Status of a Referral
Ceasing/Completing Referrals
Re-Requesting information or providing a further response to clarify

Service Behaviour

The consumer of this service will provide:
Referral Request ID
Sequence Number
To identify the referral to be modified and the changed referral data (the Delta).
This service will update the referral details.
A consumer of this service receives either:
Success Message
Or
An Enterprise Error detailing why modify was unsuccessful.

Service Variants

This service has no service variants.

Service Dependencies

This service relies on the consumer already having a unique identifier of a Visa Application as a Visa Application Id and a referral have been created.

Service Composition

Service Flow

The following service flow describes a successful execution path.

  1. The Consumer invokes the service on ESB.
  2. Consumer provides ICSE ClientId to call ICSE otherwise Service throw Exception.
  3. ESB invokes service provider ICSE for Modify Visa Application Referral.
  4. ICSE returns success message to ESB.
  5. ESB transforms ICSE response into ModifyVisaApplicationReferralResponse.
  6. ESB returns ModifyVisaApplicationReferralResponse to Consumer.

1.1.1 Alternate Flow 1
The following alternate service flow depicts the execution path that takes place when the primary provider (ICSE) raises an error.

  1. The Consumer invokes the service on ESB.
  2. Consumer provides ICSE ClientId to call ICSE otherwise Service throw Exception.
  3. ESB invokes service provider ICSE for Modify Visa Application Referral.
  4. ICSE returns response to ESB.
  5. ESB detects that ICSE has returned an error or failure message.
  6. ESB transforms ICSE error into Enterprise Error Message.
  7. ESB returns response with Enterprise Error payload to Consumer.

Service State Management Decisions

No state management required.
